<subSubSection pageId="199" pageNumber="477" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="199" pageNumber="477" targetBox="[106,698,1012,1428]" targetPageId="199">
<paragraph blockId="199.[721,1312,1005,1432]" pageId="199" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[722,897,1123,1156]" pageId="199" pageNumber="477">Distribution.</emphasis>
E Andean slopes from extreme SE Peru (Puno Department) through Bolivia to NW 
<taxonomicName box="[1074,1216,1202,1235]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Argentina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="199" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Argentina</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1244,1311,1202,1235]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Salta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="199" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Salta</taxonomicName>
and Jujuy provinces).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="199" pageNumber="477" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="199.[721,1312,1005,1432]" lastBlockId="199.[106,1313,1447,1946]" pageId="199" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[722,1007,1281,1314]" pageId="199" pageNumber="477">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 95-108 mm, tail 75-95 mm, ear 17 mm, hindfoot 21 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. The Smoky Grass Mouse is a medium-sized species of 
<taxonomicName box="[502,601,1447,1472]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Akodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="199" pageNumber="477" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Akodon</taxonomicName>
. Dorsum is dark brown, with rufous overtones; venter is similar to dorsum; and eyes are ringed with pale color. Tail is slightly bicolored.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="199" pageNumber="477" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="199.[106,1313,1447,1946]" pageId="199" pageNumber="477">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[108,219,1517,1550]" pageId="199" pageNumber="477">Habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[229,337,1517,1550]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Polylepis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="199" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Polylepis</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[356,487,1517,1550]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="199" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
) woodlands, cloud forest, and 
<taxonomicName box="[917,1063,1517,1550]" class="Pinopsida" family="Podocarpaceae" genus="Podocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="199" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Podocarpus</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1082,1298,1517,1550]" class="Pinopsida" family="Podocarpaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="199" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Podocarpaceae</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hill" authorityYear="1753" box="[170,248,1561,1590]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Alnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="199" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Alnus</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[268,423,1561,1590]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="199" pageNumber="477" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
) forests at elevations of 700 m to at least 3800 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[108,608,1600,1629]" pageId="199" pageNumber="477" type="food_feeding">
